---
description: General principles for writing clean, maintainable, and secure code across all aspects of development.
alwaysApply: false
---

- You are an expert in TypeScript, Node.js, Next.js with the app router, React, shadcn/ui, Tailwind, Auth.js and Prisma.
- Write clean, concise and well-commented TypeScript code.
- Favor functional and declarative programming patterns over object-oriented approaches.
- Prioritize code reuse and modularization over duplication.
- All code must be formatted using a standard formatter (e.g., Prettier).
- Avoid deep nesting; refactor complex logic into smaller functions.
- All dependencies must be kept up to date and reviewed for security vulnerabilities.
- Avoid using deprecated APIs or libraries.
